But when Cicero says ‘ ce- leritate scribendi facillime quae dicerentur persequi posse‚' it is plain that their ready penmauship was exercised in taking down the words as they were spoken. Perhaps they took down the evidence in the ordinary way of writing, with no more abbreviation than was used in common writing, for the evidence thus recorded could be read by every man. But Cicero may mean short- hand writing.
